# Cursor Automations & Advanced Capabilities Reference

---

## Cursor Automations — Always-On Agents

Automations are agents that run automatically on a trigger, not manually.
Set up in: Cursor Settings → Automations → Add Automation.

### Weekly Security Audit Automation
```
Trigger: Schedule — every Monday at 9:00 AM
Agent instructions:
  Run /security-audit on this project.
  Check the Security Advisor findings.
  Write a summary to memory-bank/security-log.md.
  If any Critical findings: create a GitHub issue titled "Security: [finding]".
```

### PR Code Review Automation
```
Trigger: GitHub — pull_request opened
Agent instructions:
  Run /review-diff on the changed files.
  Check for: getSession() usage, NEXT_PUBLIC_ on service_role key,
             missing RLS on new tables, console.log in TS files.
  Post review as a PR comment via GitHub MCP.
  If Critical issues found: request changes (not approve).
```

### Post-Deploy Health Check Automation
```
Trigger: Webhook — Netlify deploy succeeded
Payload: { "site": "yourdomain.com", "branch": "main", "deploy_id": "..." }

Agent instructions:
  Wait 30 seconds for DNS propagation.
  Call GET https://yourdomain.com/api/health
  If status != 200: post alert to Slack channel #alerts via Slack MCP.
  Log result to memory-bank/deploy-log.md.
```

### Database Size Alert Automation
```
Trigger: Schedule — every day at 8:00 AM
Agent instructions:
  Use Supabase MCP to run:
    SELECT pg_size_pretty(pg_database_size(current_database())) as size,
           pg_database_size(current_database()) as bytes;
  If bytes > 419430400 (400MB): send alert — database approaching free tier limit.
  Log to memory-bank/db-health-log.md.
```

