## Background Agents — Non-Blocking Workflows

For long-running tasks, use background agents instead of blocking the main conversation.

```
# In Cursor: CMD+SHIFT+P → "Run Background Agent"
# Or via automation trigger

Example background agent command:
"Implement the complete order management system in the background.
 Follow the plan in memory-bank/order-system-plan.md.
 Commit each completed component with a descriptive message.
 When done, create a PR and post the link here."

# You keep coding — the background agent works independently
# It notifies you when complete
```

### When to use background agents vs inline
```
Use inline (main chat) for:
  - Bug fixes (need immediate feedback)
  - Explaining code
  - Reviewing diffs before accepting

Use background agents for:
  - Implementing a full feature from a spec
  - Batch test writing
  - Codebase-wide refactors (rename, formatting, migration)
  - Long-running analysis
```

