## Git Worktrees — True Parallel Development

```bash
# Set up worktrees for parallel agent work
# Each worktree = isolated directory = agents can't conflict

# Create worktrees
git worktree add ../project-api-agent   feature/order-api
git worktree add ../project-ui-agent    feature/order-ui
git worktree add ../project-tests-agent feature/order-tests

# Open each in a separate Cursor window
code ../project-api-agent    # Agent 1 writes API routes
code ../project-ui-agent     # Agent 2 writes UI components
code ../project-tests-agent  # Agent 3 writes tests

# After agents complete, merge branches
git checkout main
git merge feature/order-api feature/order-ui feature/order-tests

# Clean up
git worktree remove ../project-api-agent
git worktree remove ../project-ui-agent
git worktree remove ../project-tests-agent
```

### Parallel /implement-feature pattern
```
Instead of one agent doing everything sequentially:
  1. /plan-feature → produces plan.md with API + UI + tests breakdown
  2. Open 3 worktrees
  3. Agent 1: /implement-feature (API routes only) — in worktree 1
  4. Agent 2: /implement-feature (components only)  — in worktree 2
  5. Agent 3: /yolo-tdd (tests only)               — in worktree 3
  6. Merge all three when complete
  
Result: 3x faster feature implementation with zero conflicts
```

