## Team Rules Distribution

When multiple developers use the same Rocket project, keep rules in sync.

```json
// cursor.team.json (project root — commit to git)
{
  "version": "V31",
  "rules": ".cursor/rules",
  "required_rules": [
    "rocket-cursor-behavior.mdc",
    "rocket-quick-reference.mdc"
  ],
  "shared_instincts": "memory-bank/instincts/shared",
  "sync_on_open": true
}
```

```bash
# New developer setup — after cloning the repo:
# 1. Copy .cursor/ and memory-bank/ (already in repo)
# 2. Run /check-mcp to verify MCP connections
# 3. Import team instincts:
/instinct-import memory-bank/instincts/shared/team-instincts.yaml

# Share new instincts with team:
/instinct-export > memory-bank/instincts/shared/$(date +%Y-%m-%d)-instincts.yaml
git add memory-bank/instincts/shared/
git commit -m "chore: share session instincts"
```

