## Daily Instinct Review Automation

Runs every morning, checks for high-confidence instincts ready for promotion,
and writes a notification file you can act on.

```yaml
# Full Cursor Automation YAML — paste into Settings → Automations → Add

name: Daily Instinct Review
description: Check for promotable instincts each morning and alert

trigger:
  type: schedule
  cron: "0 9 * * 1-5"          # 9 AM Monday–Friday (server local time)
  timezone: "America/New_York"  # adjust to your timezone

instructions: |
  Step 1 — Run the promoter scan:
    Execute: node .cursor/hooks/instinct-promoter.js
    Capture the output.

  Step 2 — Check for pending drafts:
    Execute: node .cursor/hooks/instinct-promoter.js --status
    Capture the count.

  Step 3 — If count > 0:
    Read every file in memory-bank/promoted-rules/ that ends in .draft.md
    and has status: pending in its frontmatter.

    Write a summary to memory-bank/instinct-review-today.md:

    ---
    # Instinct Review — [TODAY'S DATE]

    ## Ready for Promotion (N instinct(s))

    [For each pending draft, one line:]
    - `[instinct_id]` — domain: [domain] | confidence: [X] | evidence: [N]
      Action: [first sentence of the Instinct Content section]
      Auto-approves at: [auto_approve_after timestamp]

    ## How to act
    - Do nothing → each draft auto-approves after 5 minutes.
    - Cancel a promotion → delete the .draft.md file before the deadline.
    - Approve immediately → run: node .cursor/hooks/instinct-promoter.js --apply [slug]
    ---

  Step 4 — If conflicts exist (memory-bank/conflicts.md was modified today):
    Append to memory-bank/instinct-review-today.md:

    ## ⚠ Conflicts Requiring Review
    [Paste the new conflict entries from memory-bank/conflicts.md]
    These will NOT auto-promote. Manual resolution required.

  Step 5 — Notification:
    Write one line to .cursor/agent-log.txt:
    [YYYY-MM-DD 09:00] INSTINCT REVIEW: N pending, M conflicts — see memory-bank/instinct-review-today.md

  Step 6 — Optional Slack alert (if SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL is set in env):
    POST to $SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL:
    {
      "text": ":brain: *Rocket Instinct Review* — N instinct(s) ready for promotion. Check memory-bank/instinct-review-today.md"
    }
```

```bash
# Manual trigger (anytime):
node .cursor/hooks/instinct-promoter.js         # scan + auto-approve expired drafts
node .cursor/hooks/instinct-promoter.js --status # see what's pending
cat memory-bank/instinct-review-today.md         # read today's review

# Optional Slack notification setup:
# Add to .env.local (never commit):
SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL=https://hooks.slack.com/services/T.../B.../...
# Create webhook: api.slack.com/apps → Incoming Webhooks → Add New Webhook
```

