## PR Performance Gate Automation

Triggers on every new pull request. Runs `/quality-gate` and posts the results
as a PR comment using GitHub MCP.

```yaml
# Full Cursor Automation YAML — paste into Settings → Automations → Add

name: PR Performance Gate
description: Run quality checks on PR and post results as a comment

trigger:
  type: github
  event: pull_request
  actions: [opened, synchronize, reopened]
  # fires on: new PR, new commits pushed to a PR, re-opened PR

instructions: |
  A pull request was opened or updated. Run a quality gate.

  Step 1 — Get changed files:
    Use GitHub MCP tool list_pull_request_files to get the list of changed files.
    Filter to: **/*.ts, **/*.tsx, **/*.sql, **/migrations/**

  Step 2 — Run TypeScript check:
    Execute: npx tsc --noEmit 2>&1
    Count error lines. Pass = 0 errors.

  Step 3 — Security pattern scan (scan the diff or changed files):
    Check for each of these — mark FAIL if any found:
    a) getSession() used in any server-side file (app/, lib/, supabase/functions/)
    b) NEXT_PUBLIC_ prefix on service_role or secret key variable name
    c) console.log in any .ts or .tsx file (not in a comment)
    d) Any new CREATE TABLE statement in .sql files WITHOUT the following line:
       ALTER TABLE <tablename> ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;

  Step 4 — Format the result as a GitHub PR comment:

    ## Rocket Quality Gate

    | Check | Status | Detail |
    |---|---|---|
    | TypeScript | ✅ PASS / ❌ FAIL | N errors |
    | getSession() usage | ✅ PASS / ❌ FAIL | files affected or "clean" |
    | Secret exposure | ✅ PASS / ❌ FAIL | "clean" or describe issue |
    | console.log | ✅ PASS / ❌ FAIL | files with hits or "clean" |
    | RLS on new tables | ✅ PASS / ❌ FAIL | tables checked or "no new tables" |

    **Verdict: ✅ APPROVE / ❌ REQUEST CHANGES**

    [One-line summary. If all pass: "All checks passed — safe to merge."
     If any fail: "N check(s) failed — see details above before merging."]

    <sub>Automated by Rocket Quality Gate • V32</sub>

  Step 5 — Post the comment:
    Use GitHub MCP tool: create_issue_comment
    Parameters: owner, repo (from PR context), issue_number (PR number), body (the formatted comment)

  Step 6 — If verdict is REQUEST CHANGES:
    Use GitHub MCP tool: create_review
    Parameters: event = "REQUEST_CHANGES", body = "Quality gate failed. See comment above."

required_mcp_servers:
  - github    # must be enabled in Settings → Tools & MCP
```

```bash
# Setup for PR Performance Gate:

# 1. Add GitHub MCP to .cursor/mcp.json:
#    "github": {
#      "command": "npx",
#      "args": ["-y", "@modelcontextprotocol/server-github"],
#      "env": { "GITHUB_TOKEN": "ghp_..." }
#    }

# 2. Create a GitHub Personal Access Token:
#    github.com → Settings → Developer Settings → Personal Access Tokens → Fine-grained
#    Repository permissions needed:
#      Contents: Read
#      Pull requests: Read AND Write   ← required to post comments
#      Metadata: Read

# 3. NEVER commit mcp.json with the real token:
echo ".cursor/mcp.json" >> .gitignore
# Use environment variable substitution instead:
#   "GITHUB_TOKEN": "${GITHUB_TOKEN}"
# Then set GITHUB_TOKEN in your shell profile.
```
